        "text_html": "<p>Updated story to 'Scene 1 \u2014 The Guardian of Blackstone Pass</p>\n\n<p>The story opens high in Blackstone Pass, where an ancient mountain road winds between sheer cliffs toward the Shrine of the First Mothers. Morning fog still clings to the stone, and the silence is broken only by distant ravens. Rugor is already present before the first panel, kneeling beside the road with one gauntleted hand resting on the earth. She is not tracking prey in the conventional sense. Instead, she is reconstructing events. Deep ruts in the soil reveal a heavily laden wagon. Fresh boot prints indicate eight armed travelers. Broken arrow shafts suggest a brief fight, yet there are remarkably few bloodstains. Rugor concludes that whoever attacked the wagon wanted captives rather than corpses. She rises without a word and continues toward the shrine. The reader immediately understands that she thinks before she moves, and that observation is her primary weapon.</p>\n\n<p>Several miles farther along the trail, Rugor discovers the survivors rather than the attackers. A merchant family has barricaded themselves beneath an overturned wagon. The father raises a spear as Rugor approaches, assuming that any troll must be part of the ambush. Rugor does not react to the threat. Instead, she notices the man\u2019s trembling hands, the broken axle, the empty quivers, and the frightened children trying to remain silent beneath a blanket. She deliberately plants her polearm in the ground several paces away before speaking. That singl</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      },
      {
        "name": "the Editor",
        "text_html": "<p>Here\u2019s a clean <strong>scene breakdown</strong> of this issue\u2019s own story (THE SCRIPT), in production terms. Approve this list and I\u2019ll move on to settings/cast verification and then create the scenes in the issue.</p>\n\n<h2>Proposed scenes (for approval)</h2>\n\n<h3>1) Blackstone Pass Tracks</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Setting:</strong> EXT. Blackstone Pass mountain road (approach to shrine)</li>\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> morning</li>\n<li><strong>Mood:</strong> cold, quiet, investigative; fog-muted light</li>\n<li><strong>Cast:</strong> Rugor; Merchant Father; Merchant Mother; 2\u20133 frightened children (background)</li>\n<li><strong>Props:</strong> Rugor\u2019s polearm; overturned/barricade wagon; spear; broken arrows; bootprints/ruts</li>\n<li><strong>Blocking:</strong> Rugor kneels and reads the ground; later approaches survivors slowly, plants polearm away to signal peace; brief Q&A; then continues uphill alone.</li>\n<li><strong>Scene story (2\u20134 sentences):</strong> Rugor reconstructs an ambush from traces on the road and concludes captives were taken. She finds a merchant family hiding under an overturned wagon; they report grave robbers entered the Shrine of the First Mothers before dawn and attacked witnesses. Rugor learns the rough count and timing, then heads for the shrine, already thinking in causes and consequences.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>2) Shrine Threshold</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Setting:</strong> EXT. Shrine of the First Mothers entrance</li>\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> late morning</li>\n<li><strong>Mood:</strong> wrongness, hushed dread; air feels \u201copened\u201d</li>\n<li><strong>Cast:</strong> Rugor; 2 unconscious troll wardens (non-speaking)</li>\n<li><strong>Props:</strong> bronze doors ajar; warden weapons scattered; mixed bootprints; Squonk\u2019s erratic small tracks</li>\n<li><strong>Blocking:</strong> Rugor checks wardens, studies prints; long beat of silent deduction; then steps over threshold deliberately.</li>\n<li><strong>Scene story:</strong> Rugor finds the shrine doors ajar and wardens incapacitated with professional precision. She notices a second, absurd trail of small feet looping and doubling back\u2014someone blundering inside after the mercenaries. Accepting there\u2019s an unknown variable still alive in the dark, she enters, choosing understanding before judgment.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>3) Squonk at Work</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Setting:</strong> INT. Shrine corridors/anterooms (deeper interior travel)</li>\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> continuous (interior dim)</li>\n<li><strong>Mood:</strong> comic-chaotic, scrappy, precarious luck</li>\n<li><strong>Cast:</strong> Squonk (solo)</li>\n<li><strong>Props:</strong> red cloak; oversized pack; \u201cfound\u201d trinkets; odd bronze key; ancient traps (implied)</li>\n<li><strong>Blocking:</strong> Squonk narrates himself while physically bungling through\u2014snagging cloak, bumping pillars, loudly \u201csneaking\u201d\u2014yet accidentally avoids traps via impulse choices.</li>\n<li><strong>Scene story:</strong> We meet Squonk\u2019s self-mythologizing thief persona, contrasted with visuals showing incompetence and desperation. He\u2019s hunting one sellable object to eat and sleep indoors. His chaotic intuition keeps him alive, steering him around traps without him understanding why.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>4) Vault Chamber Observation</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Setting:</strong> INT. Vault chamber (big central room)</li>\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> continuous</li>\n<li><strong>Mood:</strong> tense, clinical professionalism vs. Squonk\u2019s opportunism</li>\n<li><strong>Cast:</strong> Squonk; Ash Company team (6 mercenaries, including a leader; 1\u20132 engineer-types)</li>\n<li><strong>Props:</strong> sealed stone vault; specialized iron tools; maps; hand-signal discipline; altar with ceremonial dagger</li>\n<li><strong>Blocking:</strong> Squonk hides behind statuary/pillars; watches their methodical setup; eyes drift to unattended valuables; reaches for altar dagger at the end.</li>\n<li><strong>Scene story:</strong> Squonk discovers the real heist: the Ash Company is opening a sealed vault with prepared gear and discipline. He decides to wait and steal after they do the hard work. He can\u2019t resist a ceremonial dagger on an altar\u2014reaching for it just as we reveal Rugor has been silently watching him.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>5) Interrupted Theft (Rugor + Squonk)</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Setting:</strong> INT. Vault chamber, near altar and sightline to vault</li>\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> continuous</li>\n<li><strong>Mood:</strong> controlled restraint; quiet intimidation without cruelty</li>\n<li><strong>Cast:</strong> Rugor; Squonk; Ash Company in background</li>\n<li><strong>Props:</strong> ceremonial dagger; Squonk\u2019s knife; Squonk\u2019s pack contents (needles/mushrooms/twine/bread); Ash Company tools</li>\n<li><strong>Blocking:</strong> Rugor\u2019s hand settles over Squonk\u2019s to stop the dagger; she keeps eyes on mercenaries; brief whispered interrogation; she \u201canchors\u201d his attention; they watch the team work; Rugor whispers \u201cDon\u2019t\u201d as the vault rises and a purse is set down.</li>\n<li><strong>Scene story:</strong> Rugor stops Squonk from stealing and calmly interrogates why he\u2019s here, reading his poverty through his gear. She explains the Ash Company threat and the stakes\u2014records of lineage and treaties\u2014while demonstrating how disciplined enemies think. The vault begins to rise; Squonk spots an \u201ceasy\u201d purse and slips away despite Rugor\u2019s warning.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>6) The Wrong Thing Happens</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Setting:</strong> INT. Vault chamber, among columns/pillars near mechanism</li>\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> moments later</li>\n<li><strong>Mood:</strong> sudden catastrophe; stone screaming; panic</li>\n<li><strong>Cast:</strong> Rugor; Squonk; Ash Company (leader + men)</li>\n<li><strong>Props:</strong> ornate \u201cpurse\u201d containing bronze locking pin/cylinder with runes; vault lifting mechanism; crossbow bolt impact; falling stone/dust</li>\n<li><strong>Blocking:</strong> Squonk successfully steals, then opens the purse too soon; the pin snaps loudly; mechanism jams; mercenaries scramble; Rugor yanks Squonk into cover as they start hunting for saboteur.</li>\n<li><strong>Scene story:</strong> Squonk\u2019s theft \u201cworks\u201d until he discovers he stole a locking pin, not coins, and accidentally re-extends it with a metallic crack that jams the ancient mechanism. The chamber destabilizes\u2014cracks, falling debris, screaming gears\u2014forcing everyone into emergency response. A new sound rises: heavy rhythmic impacts from below, implying the vault is a prison and something is trying to get out.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>7) The Hunt Begins (Rugor takes initiative)</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Setting:</strong> INT. Vault chamber (now damaged/unstable)</li>\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> continuous</li>\n<li><strong>Mood:</strong> command vs. greed; moral line in the dust</li>\n<li><strong>Cast:</strong> Rugor; Ash Company captain/leader; engineers; crossbowmen; Squonk</li>\n<li><strong>Props:</strong> exposed locking bars beneath floor; Rugor\u2019s polearm used as lever/indicator; bronze locking pin (in Squonk\u2019s possession)</li>\n<li><strong>Blocking:</strong> Rugor strides into open and orders them to stop; demonstrates structural truth by striking a seam and exposing bars; captain argues speed; Rugor plants herself between engineers and mechanism, refusing further tampering.</li>\n<li><strong>Scene story:</strong> The mercenaries try to \u201cfinish the opening\u201d to control whatever is inside; Rugor argues the containment system is already compromised and forcing it will collapse the prison. She proves it physically by exposing the locking bars, briefly making them hesitate. The captain rejects her anyway; Rugor shifts from observer to obstacle, drawing a hard line: nobody touches the prison again.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>8) A Deliberate Choice (Dawn judgment / partnership formed)</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Setting:</strong> EXT. Blackstone Pass outside shrine, aftermath</li>\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> dawn</li>\n<li><strong>Mood:</strong> exhausted, moral clarity, consequential calm</li>\n<li><strong>Cast:</strong> Rugor; Squonk; tribal elders; surviving wardens/guards (background)</li>\n<li><strong>Props:</strong> guardian\u2019s torque (Rugor\u2019s insignia); bundled supplies; pots/rope spilling from Squonk\u2019s sack</li>\n<li><strong>Blocking:</strong> Elders hold Squonk; Rugor testifies\u2014confirms facts then reframes intent/consequence; elders offer compromise; Rugor removes torque and resigns; on road, she silently takes weight from Squonk and matches pace beside him.</li>\n<li><strong>Scene story:</strong> After the fight and stabilization, elders move to punish Squonk as a desecrator. Rugor gives a truthful account that also insists on weighing intent and consequence; when the elders refuse, she resigns rather than participate in injustice. She chooses to travel with Squonk, not as a reward, but as a deliberate act of compassion\u2014walking side by side down the pass.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>One critique before you approve: <strong>Scene 2 (Shrine Threshold) and Scene 3 (Squonk at Work) could be merged</strong>, but keeping them separate helps the tonal snap and gives Rugor a clean \u201ccrossing the threshold\u201d button.</p>\n\n<p>Approve this scene list as-is? (yes/no)</p>\n",
