        "text_html": "<p>[CharacterModel(character<em>id='6a337a36-8dc6-46af-a3dd-484a0593dcd1', series</em>id='3e3fdb21-8f39-42ff-add7-6fbdda798a21', description='Squonk is Rugor\u2019s cowardly orc thief sidekick, always hovering at the edge of danger and looking for the quickest exit. Smaller than most orcs, he compensates with constant scheming, petty larceny, and a talent for getting into trouble he can\u2019t fight his way out of.\\n\\nHe has a pig-like snout, boarish tusks, thinning hair, and only three fingers on each hand\u2014traits that make him look half-feral even when he\u2019s trying to pass as \u201charmless.\u201d Squonk is colorblind and insists his red cloak and purple tunic are perfect for stealth because he truly believes they blend in, which only makes him easier to spot and more defensive about it.\\n\\nSquonk is exceptionally bad at thieving in a consistent, slapstick way: clumsy, loud, and obvious, forever snagging his cloak, knocking things over, and dropping loot right after he steals it. To hype himself up (and accidentally give himself away), he talks to himself in the third person\u2014\"He gets the tools. He opens the chest. He escapes unnoticed!\"\u2014often at exactly the wrong volume.\\n\\nRugor mostly responds with long-suffering eye rolls and silent course-corrections. She keeps him around not because he\u2019s useful, but because she understands what it is to be treated like an outcast; she only shows it when it matters, quietly bailing him out while Squonk credits his own \"perfect\" getaway.', name='Squonk', origin=None), </p>\n",
