        "name": "the Editor",
        "text_html": "<p>Created publisher <strong>Mythforge</strong>.  </p>\n\n<p>Here\u2019s a fleshed-out, author-facing description (you can tell me what to tighten or change):</p>\n\n<p><strong>Mythforge</strong> publishes YA-to-adult comics that reimagine classic epics\u2014<em>The Iliad</em>, <em>Beowulf</em>, and other mythic source texts\u2014as modern or futuristic dramas. We\u2019re for creators who want the emotional weight, stakes, and archetypes of foundational literature without being trapped by period accuracy. Mythforge favors bold reinterpretations, culturally aware retellings, and genre blends (near\u2011future, cyberpunk, space opera, contemporary political drama) that still honor the structural \u201cbones\u201d of the original story.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Rights &amp; ownership:</strong> Mythforge is creator-friendly. Creators retain ownership of their intellectual property; Mythforge licenses publishing rights for specific formats/territories/terms. Adaptation and merchandising rights remain with creators unless separately negotiated.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Formats &amp; distribution:</strong> We develop projects for digital-first release and high-quality print editions (single issues, collected trades, and occasional deluxe hardcovers when demand supports it). Distribution targets comic shops and direct-to-reader channels, with selective bookstore placement for collected editions and strong international digital storefront presence.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Editorial approach:</strong> Editorial is hands-on and story-forward\u2014developmental notes, pacing/continuity support, and sensitivity-minded feedback when adapting culturally significant material. The goal is clarity and momentum, not sanding down a creator\u2019s voice.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Marketing &amp; promotion:</strong> Mythforge supports launches with cover reveals, press outreach, retailer materials, and ready-to-use social assets. Creators are expected to participate (interviews, process posts, conventions when feasible). Positioning stays hook-forward: \u201cepic literature meets modern drama,\u201d with a clear reader promise.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Compensation:</strong> Deals are royalty-based from net receipts, with performance escalators for strong sales. Advances are project-dependent and typically reserved for proven teams or flagship launches.</p>\n\n<p>One question: do you want Mythforge framed as <strong>creator-owned only</strong>, or are you open to <strong>Mythforge-owned</strong> originals as well?</p>\n",
