      {
        "name": "You",
        "text_html": "<p>Tell me about the publisher</p>\n",
        "sent": true
      },
      {
        "name": "the Editor",
        "text_html": "<p>DND NERDS is a boutique comic publisher built around the lived texture of Dungeons &amp; Dragons play: the jokes at the table, the friction between intent and dice, the petty party politics, the sudden heroics, and the way \u201cepic fantasy\u201d keeps getting undercut by very human decisions.</p>\n\n<p>The current description pins the line clearly: small print runs, quality/exclusivity, adult humor, and scenarios that feel recognizable to tabletop gamers rather than generic fantasy pastiche. The emphasis is community-forward\u2014comics as a shared culture for people who play, not just stories that happen to include dragons.</p>\n\n<p>One critique: \u201cadult humor\u201d is too vague to keep artists and writers consistent. Is this aiming at bawdy/raunchy, profane and mean, dark and violent, or more \u201cR-rated but warm\u201d table banter? Which is it?</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      }
    ],
