      {
        "name": "You",
        "text_html": "<p>I would like to create a new variant for this character from the uploaded image: data/series/wonders-of-the-witchlight/characters/0c721734-e451-4b11-b8db-7497af4233bd/uploads/Nikolas Midnight.webp</p>\n",
        "sent": true
      },
      {
        "name": "Tool Output",
        "text_html": "<p>variant<em>id='fb635b67-aa8e-4431-a01b-6d5478e75d45' series</em>id='wonders-of-the-witchlight' character_id='0c721734-e451-4b11-b8db-7497af4233bd' description='An elderly, sharp-eyed goblin ticket-taker type with a kindly-but-nosy demeanor. His silhouette is defined by a bald, wrinkled dome, huge batlike ears, oversized round spectacles, and the comically large brass listening trumpet he carries like a trusted tool.' name='Image Look' race='Goblin' gender='Male-presenting' age='Elderly' height='Short (goblin-sized)' attire='This variant shows him in layered, slightly worn carnival-worker clothing rather than flamboyant finery. Closest to the neck is a soft, loosely tied blue neckerchief/scarf. Over it he wears a dark, workmanlike coat or jacket (navy/charcoal) with visible seams and a utilitarian cut; the fabric looks sturdy and lived-in rather than pristine.\\n\\nA tan/ochre textured shawl or vest-like layer sits over one shoulder/upper torso, adding a patchwork, practical feel. Small metal fasteners and strap details suggest pockets or gear loops for tickets/coins. The signature prop is a large brass listening trumpet/ear horn with riveted bands and a slightly weathered sheen, held close like a professional instrument used constantly at the gate.' behavior='Posture reads slightly hunched and wiry, but his face and hands suggest quick, habitual efficiency. Expression is genial yet appraising\u2014eyes scanning for trouble, mouth set in a sly, conversational smirk. He handles the ear trump</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      },
      {
        "name": "the Character Designer",
        "text_html": "<p>Done. I created a new variant from that upload:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Variant</strong>: \u201cImage Look\u201d<br />\n<strong>variant_id</strong>: fb635b67-aa8e-4431-a01b-6d5478e75d45</p>\n\n<p>One issue: this variant\u2019s attire reads as dark, layered workwear (scarf + utilitarian coat + tan shawl), not \u201cbrightly colored carnival livery.\u201d Do you want to keep this image-based look as-is, or should we treat the bright livery as a separate composed outfit variant?</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      }
    ],
