      {
        "name": "You",
        "text_html": "<p>I would like to create a new variant for this character from the uploaded image: data/series/wonders-of-the-witchlight/characters/37d463fe-9815-4eac-9386-b7eb7e63dc25/uploads/Dianna Cloppington.jpeg</p>\n",
        "sent": true
      },
      {
        "name": "Tool Output",
        "text_html": "<p>variant<em>id='81e5dd68-c387-4570-8785-fae6369ca327' series</em>id='wonders-of-the-witchlight' character_id='37d463fe-9815-4eac-9386-b7eb7e63dc25' description='A poised, carnival-fantasy centaur woman fused with a piebald mount and adorned with oversized butterfly wings. Her look blends whimsical faerie pageantry (bright patterns, wings, floral accent) with a grounded, work-ready stance\u2014arms folded, expression calm but guarded.' name='from photo' race='Fey-touched centaur (piebald horse body) with butterfly wings' gender='Female' age='Adult (late 20s\u201330s)' height='Tall; ~7\u20138 ft at head (centaur scale)' attire='Carnival-fantasy outfit in saturated jewel tones. She wears a fitted bodice/corset in purples and blues with a pinkish decorative element at the chest (brooch or laced detail). Sleeves are long and striped (blue and purple), giving a harlequin/carnival feel; shoulders are capped with warm orange-gold accents.\\n\\nA draped, tabard-like cloth hangs over the front of the equine body, patterned with bold purple and blue flame/chevron motifs, edged to look like layered fabric panels. She has gold bands/anklets above the hooves and dark hoof coverings/shoe-like caps, maintaining a uniform, \u201cstaff\u201d polish while still fantastical.' behavior='Professional and self-contained; typically stands squarely with arms crossed, projecting calm authority at the gate. Expression reads approachable but cautious\u2014helpful on the surface, with an undercurrent of restraint as if carefully choosing words</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      },
      {
        "name": "the Character Designer",
        "text_html": "<p>Created the new variant from your uploaded image.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Character: Dianna Cloppington  </li>\n<li>Variant name: <strong>from photo</strong>  </li>\n<li>Variant id: <strong>81e5dd68-c387-4570-8785-fae6369ca327</strong>  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>One issue: this variant currently includes full attire text inline (and no outfit asset). Do you want me to extract its wardrobe into a reusable Outfit asset (so future looks can be composed cleanly)?</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      }
