      {
        "name": "Tool Output",
        "text_html": "<p>[CharacterVariant(variant<em>id='5214107a-27d4-47ae-b780-0c6d24c82f86', series</em>id='3e3fdb21-8f39-42ff-add7-6fbdda798a21', character_id='6a337a36-8dc6-46af-a3dd-484a0593dcd1', description='Squonk\u2019s baseline look: a small, nervous orc thief who tries to look stealthy and competent but is immediately conspicuous. This is the everyday version of him seen trailing Rugor\u2014always half-crouched, always ready to bolt, and always convinced he\u2019s pulling off a perfect crime. His colorblind fashion choices make him stand out even more, fueling his defensive swagger.', name='Base', race='orc', gender='male', age='adult', height='short', attire='He wears a bright red cloak that he insists is perfect for stealth, draped over a purple tunic that clashes badly to everyone but him. The cloak is scuffed and frequently snagged at the hem, and the tunic is sweat-darkened at the collar and patched in a few places. He pairs this with rough trousers, a belt cinched with mismatched buckles, and battered boots meant for quiet steps but usually failing at it.\\n\\nHis belt and shoulders carry petty-thief clutter: small pouches, bits of cord, and a simple set of lockpicks and prying tools that rattle if he moves too fast. Nothing about his outfit is heroic\u2014everything looks secondhand, ill-chosen, and worn from repeated botched escapes.', behavior='Squonk is cowardly and constantly on the lookout for exits, hovering at the edge of danger and flinching at sudden noises. He tries to hype himself into bravery by t</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      },
