        "text_html": "<p>I can\u2019t from here: the scene tool says this scene/panel isn\u2019t in my current tool context, so I can\u2019t read/update the scene setting or render a new take.</p>\n\n<p>Select this exact panel again in the studio UI (Series <strong>Rugor</strong> \u2192 Issue <strong>Guardian of Blackstone Pass</strong> \u2192 Scene <strong>Pass Tracks</strong> \u2192 Panel <strong>Rugor Reads The Ground</strong>), then tell me \u201cgo on\u201d and I\u2019ll:\n- set the scene setting to <strong>Blackstone Pass Road</strong> (master background),\n- keep Rugor variant <strong>331296d6-883d-417b-928c-747d6064e84c</strong> and re-pose her to match the table blocking (60% from left, mid-ground),\n- render a new take and letter it exactly as blocked.</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      },
      {
        "name": "the Inker",
        "text_html": "<p>\u23f3 <strong>proofing this panel \u2014 a new take</strong> \u2014 on the drawing board\u2026 (1/1)</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      },
      {
        "name": "the Inker",
        "text_html": "<p>\ud83c\udfa8 <strong>proofing this panel \u2014 a new take</strong> \u2014 done (1/1).</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      },
      {
        "name": "the Inker",
        "text_html": "<p>\ud83d\uddbc\ufe0f That's the batch: 1 rendered.</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      },
