      {
        "name": "Tool Output",
        "text_html": "<p>Updated logo to 'Logo concept: a modern, minimal, Picasso\u2019s-bull\u2013like emblem of a phoenix rising vertically from the smoke and ashes of a clearly readable forge/furnace. Rendered as a few bold, separate shapes (not a continuous stroke), but with predominantly curved, organic forms rather than angular facets. Overall silhouette should fit a roughly square badge.</p>\n\n<p>Phoenix: epic \u201crebirth/evolution\u201d tone; simplified, geometric-modern construction expressed through smooth curves; very restrained feather detail; vertical upward motion is unmistakable.</p>\n\n<p>Smoke: the phoenix and its smoke plume should be integrated visually\u2014curved, minimal forms that feel like a single upward breath of heat and rebirth, with clean negative spaces.</p>\n\n<p>Forge: unmistakably a forge/furnace opening at the base, but kept no more detailed than the bird; simplified curved contours; reads quickly as the source of heat/creation rather than a realistic industrial illustration.</p>\n\n<p>Color: primarily greys and blues for the phoenix/forge/smoke (cool, modern). One single accent thread of orange/red: a thin spiral ember-filament that originates in the forge opening and rises upward, visually feeding/transforming into the phoenix (continuous ember-coil).</p>\n\n<p>Type: no wordmark, masthead, or typeface included in the logo mark.' for Publisher with ID '{'publisher_id': '226b4d80-482c-48c3-9e09-0eca1350fe8a'}'.</p>\n",
