      },
      {
        "name": "the Character Designer",
        "text_html": "<p>He\u2019s described as a demon-descended \u201cmearcstapa\u201d (a border-walker), an outcast thing that haunts the margins.</p>\n\n<p>Physically, he\u2019s a man-shaped monster: huge, massively strong, clawed-handed, and ugly enough that the poem treats his body as an affront more than a catalog of features. He comes out of the moors and fens at night, moves with stealth and certainty, and can snatch adult warriors like prey.</p>\n\n<p>Behaviorally, he\u2019s driven by hate and grievance\u2014he attacks Heorot because the sound of joy (the hall\u2019s songs, the scop\u2019s recital of creation) torments him. He doesn\u2019t raid for wealth or rule; he kills to silence the hall and to feed, leaving bodies mangled and carried off. He\u2019s also marked as uncanny: weapons often can\u2019t bite him (the poem attributes this to a kind of magic/curse), and his strength is such that he can tear open the hall\u2019s door with his hands.</p>\n\n<p>One precise question: do you want our \u201cGrendel Strain Hunter\u201d to keep the \u201cjoy-hating, hall-silencing\u201d motive, or shift it to a purely engineered mission objective?</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      },
      {
        "name": "You",
        "text_html": "<p>Prehensile claw hands (two pairs of opposable claws).   4 arms.   Yellow glowing cat like eyes.    Gaping mouth with lizard like tongue and multiple rows of shark like teeth.   Slick wet greenish mottled skin.   sparse white fur on arms back and head.   ostrich/bird like legs.</p>\n",
        "sent": true
      },
