      {
        "name": "Tool Output",
        "text_html": "<p>[CharacterVariant(variant<em>id='a21e6e21-8e3a-468b-b998-e4288686478c', series</em>id='9eea770b-f7f3-429b-b9a1-22beb98e6efe', character_id='6b2c7f35-fb11-4106-b44d-5926c76b9694', description='This is the original, definitive Grendel Strain Hunter phenotype deployed on Heorot: a purpose-built night predator engineered to exploit settlement routines and blind zones. It reads as a man-shaped intruder at a distance, but resolves into an unnervingly asymmetric, multi-limbed anatomy optimized for climbing, grappling, and rapid kills. Its presence is wet, quiet, and deliberate\u2014less feral rage than directed intent. This base variant defines its identity; other looks should be composed via outfits/props rather than re-described.', name='base', race='engineered predator-organism', gender='none', age='adult', height='tall', attire='None. The organism is deployed without clothing or armor; its exterior is the weapon system. Any added gear, harnessing, or containment apparatus should be handled as an Outfit asset and composed onto this base look.', behavior='Moves with controlled, deliberate economy\u2014stillness punctuated by sudden bursts of speed. It favors ambush, vertical approach routes, and close-quarters grappling where it can immobilize and dismember quickly. It tests thresholds, doors, and blind corners like it has learned routines, then commits with precision rather than frenzy. In close proximity it uses its hands to seize, pin, and manipulate; the eyes stay fixed on targets in a way tha</p>\n",
        "sent": false
      },
      {
        "name": "the Character Designer",
        "text_html": "<p>I can\u2019t update the <strong>base variant\u2019s</strong> description/physical description with the tools I have here: there\u2019s no <code>update_variant</code> tool exposed\u2014only <code>create_variant</code>, <code>compose_character_variant</code>, and delete/extract tools.</p>\n\n<p>What I <em>can</em> do right now is create a <strong>new base variant</strong> with the corrected text, but that would violate identity continuity (two \u201cbases\u201d), unless we delete the old base variant first.</p>\n\n<p>One question: do you want me to <strong>delete</strong> the current base variant (<code>a21e6e21-8e3a-468b-b998-e4288686478c</code>) and then recreate it with the updated description and explicit <strong>four arms + prehensile claw-hands</strong> details?</p>\n",
